@startuml current_001_component_layers
title UC Life Sim - current component layers (HEAD)

' Rule: data flows DOWN. Upward edges (and violations) are flagged red.
' The diagram is a strict vertical stack: each rank is one layer.
' Hidden edges form the ranking spine so PlantUML can't sprawl horizontally.
' ASCII-only labels (em-dashes garble under Java's default Windows charset).

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName "Inter, sans-serif"
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam ranksep 18
skinparam nodesep 35
skinparam rectangle {
  BorderColor #888
  FontSize 12
}
top to bottom direction

' --- rank 0: declarations + composition root ---
together {
  rectangle "config\n.json5 -> loaders, read once at boot"          as L_CFG  #f3f6fa
  rectangle "boot\nmain.tsx :: ScopedRoot"                          as L_BOOT #ffffff
}
rectangle "data\nstatic content (scenes, jobs, ships, ...)"          as L_DATA #f3f6fa
rectangle "procgen\npure, seeded -- roads -> blocks -> cells"        as L_PROC #eef5ee
rectangle "ecs\nkoota traits + Map<SceneId, World>"                  as L_ECS  #fff8ec
together {
  rectangle "ai\nmistreevous BT (trees + agent)"                     as L_AI   #fff3e6
  rectangle "sim\nclock, scene, loop, ship, transition"              as L_SIM  #fff3e6
}
rectangle "systems\n28 files (vitals, work, npc, combat, ...)"       as L_SYS  #fff3e6
together {
  rectangle "save\nidb-keyval + superjson"                           as L_SAVE #f0e6ff
  rectangle "render\npixi + sprite + portrait"                       as L_REND #e9f3ff
}
rectangle "ui\nReact DOM + zustand stores"                           as L_UI   #e9f3ff

' --- hidden ranking spine: forces strict vertical stack ---
L_CFG  -[hidden]-> L_DATA
L_BOOT -[hidden]-> L_DATA
L_DATA -[hidden]-> L_PROC
L_PROC -[hidden]-> L_ECS
L_ECS  -[hidden]-> L_AI
L_ECS  -[hidden]-> L_SIM
L_AI   -[hidden]-> L_SYS
L_SIM  -[hidden]-> L_SYS
L_SYS  -[hidden]-> L_SAVE
L_SYS  -[hidden]-> L_REND
L_SAVE -[hidden]-> L_UI
L_REND -[hidden]-> L_UI

' --- intended (downward) dependency direction ---
L_CFG  --> L_DATA
L_DATA --> L_PROC
L_DATA --> L_ECS
L_PROC --> L_ECS
L_ECS  --> L_SIM
L_AI   --> L_SYS
L_SIM  --> L_SYS
L_SYS  --> L_REND
L_SYS  --> L_SAVE
L_REND --> L_UI
L_BOOT --> L_REND
L_BOOT --> L_UI

' --- violations / concerns (red) ---
' Former save <-> sim/loop import cycle (autosave + stopLoop/startLoop)
' was severed via sim/events.ts: save emits 'load:start'/'load:end', loop
' emits 'day:rollover'/'hyperspeed:start', and src/boot/autosaveBinding
' subscribes for autosave. save no longer imports from sim/loop; sim/loop
' no longer imports from save.
'
' Per-subsystem reach was inverted via src/save/registry.ts: each persisted
' subsystem (clock, population, ship, space, combat, engagement, scene)
' has a handler in src/boot/saveHandlers/ that registers itself. save/
' iterates handlers blindly — it does not import from systems/, sim/scene,
' sim/clock, sim/engagement. Adding a 16th persisted subsystem == one
' new file in src/boot/saveHandlers/, no edit to save/index.ts.
L_BOOT -[#red]-> L_SYS  : (V) __uclife__ DEV surface\nreaches ~15 subsystems

note right of L_SYS
  Module-level singletons in:
  combat, population, relations,
  npc (buckets), activeZone, vitals,
  stress, supplyDrain, spaceSim,
  engagement.
  Not per-world. Works only because
  the world count is fixed and small.
end note

note right of L_REND
  render/ has its own internal seam:
   - Game.tsx + ground/PixiGroundRenderer
     (ECS snapshot -> pixi)
   - sprite/ (LPC composer, anim ticker)
   - portrait/ (FC pregmod port -- opaque
     core, UC owns bridge + adapter)
  See 005_render_flow + 006_portrait_pipeline.
end note

@enduml
